data.event: Historically home to the Kumeyaay people, San Diego was the first site visited by Europeans on what is now the West Coast of the United States.
Upon landing in San Diego Bay in 1542, Juan Rodríguez Cabrillo claimed the entire area for Spain, forming the basis for the settlement of Alta California 200 years later.
The Presidio and Mission of San Diego, founded in 1769, formed the first European settlement in what is now California.
